      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"2. COURT IN A STORM scored a maiden hurdle at this venue last spring. Finished a fair fourth on seasonal debut at Exeter last month. Entitled to do much better with that run behind. The one to beat. 1. QUEENS VENTURE had a useful strike rate for her previous stable. Pulled up on last outing in December. Went well fresh before while new yard managed to strike with their latest runner. May feature. 6. GRANGECLARE DIEGO might have a bit more to do on form however Harry Cobden is a very interesting jockey booking so a check in the market is warranted. Veteran 4. I'M A STARMAN was a four time winner last year and is edging back to a handy mark.\",\"runners\":[2,1,6,4],\"exclusive\":false}",
